249
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,989
No, the fair owner herself.

250
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,913
- May l look?
- Sr. Douglas...

251
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:10,036
l wonder if you'd do me a great favor?

252
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,994
Yes.

253
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,035
Then, pray present me
to this young lady.

254
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,193
- Miss Todd?
- Yes?

255
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:23,237
May l present one
of the leading lawyers of Springfield

256
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:26,193
Mr. Abraham Lincoln?

257
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:28,879
Mr. Lincoln!

258
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:37,397
Miss Todd l wonder
if you'd honor me with the next dance?

259
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:41,312
Why,... why...

260
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,552
l'd be delighted.

261
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,230
Miss Todd, you thought my face was funny,

262
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,993
and the way l dressed even funnier,

263
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,514
but the joke's on you.

264
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,399
Why, l don't understand.

265
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:01,078
Wait till you dance with me.

266
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:33,157
Have you got the license, Mr. Lincoln?

267
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,188
Well, she got you.

268
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:48,148
l knew she would
when she started out the first time for you.

269
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:49,668
Now, Billie, don't bother me.

270
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,836
l'm going to be married
and l'm scared to death.

271
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,194
Oh, don't be alarmed.

272
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,436
There's many a bite
that's worse than a bride's.

273
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:00,391
But, Billie,
that woman scares me.

274
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,834
She's even got the ridiculous idea
that l could get to be president.

275
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,956
Oh, don't take that seriously.

276
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:13,118
Every spunky girl thinks
that her husband ought to be president.

277
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,556
l know, Billie,
but it's a pity to fool her.

278
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:17,473
And she's a fine woman,

279
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:19,910
smart as pepper and pretty too.

280
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,878
She'll be a great help to you, Mr. Lincoln,

281
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,111
but you've got to keep
climbing with her.

282
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,876
Yes... yes, l know.

283
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:30,036
l've got the best supper
you've ever tasted

284
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:33,033
and the cake...

285
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,033
wait till you see that cake!

286
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:37,117
What can have happened
to Mr.Lincoln? lt's long after the...

287
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,310
He would be late at his own wedding.

288
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,548
Now, never mind, Mary,

289
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:44,194
if he doesn't come soon,
l'll send John after him.

290
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,952
But he's hours late already!

291
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,468
Think of that!

292
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:50,068
Sister, calm yourself.

293
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,191
For heaven's sakes,
you've got to hurry!

294
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:59,873
Billie, you... you go ahead.
You go on over and l'll come later.

295
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:04,271
l doubt if there's a word in the
dictionary that could tell how l feel!

296
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:08,639
Billie, what does a man do
if his head's all right

297
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,319
but his legs are cowardly?

298
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,873
My cure is to get drunk.

299
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:15,718
My legs are too frightened
to pay any attentión to liquor.

300
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:17,952
l'll go ahead and
tell them that you're coming.

301
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:32,474
Anne!

302
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:38,869
Anne!

303
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,388
Anne!

304
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,474
We looked, everywhere,
tort we can't find him.

305
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:53,955
No, can't find him...
not at the office.

306
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,639
What on earth happened to him?

307
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,751
He was in a terrible
state when l left him.

308
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:01,231
He was so frightened and upset.
l imagine he just ran away.

309
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:05,792
Ran away... from me!
On our weddin' day!

310
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,194
Now sistern dear...

311
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,554
Don't 'sister' me!

312
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:13,794
Can you imagine! That's what a Todd gets
for engagin' herself to a country baboon!

313
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,554
- Listen, dear, you mustn't...
- You may as well all go home!

314
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,236
You hear me?
You may as well all go home!

315
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:20,788
Not goin' to be any weddin' here.

316
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,558
You can all go home
as far as l'm concerned!

317
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,797
But this is so distressing!

318
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:32,796
You certainly are a matchmaker

319
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:36,073
to reconcile those two after
what happened two years ago.

320
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,878
We all like Mr. Lincoln,

321
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:40,714
and Mary is just
the girl to push him along.

322
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,634
Oh, Mary, how sweet you look!

323
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:46,034
What a lovely dress!

324
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:48,470
Yes, and so becoming to her too.

325
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,718
Maybe that's Mr. Lincoln now.

326
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:54,870
Julia it all seems so strange
having things end this way.

327
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:58,437
lt's just as it should end. You and
Mr. Lincoln will make a great man.

328
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,351
Good morning, Mr. Lincoln.

329
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:04,114
Good morning.

330
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:09,919
Come, my dear
we'll leave the happy pair alone.

331
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,389
Good morning, Mary.

332
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:18,396
l,... l...

333
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:25,630
Mary, you don't have
to bother about me any more.

334
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:28,036
l think l've settled down at last.

335
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:32,192
l hope l can make
your future all you desire.

336
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,795
We'll say no more about it, Mr. Lincoln.

337
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:39,111
l really think, after all, you need me.

338
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:45,119
You'll need a lot of patience
to put up with me, Mary,

339
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:49,909
but if anyone can do it,
l'm sure you're the one.

340
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,388
Oh, Mary!

341
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:33,150
Douglas is a prize speaker,

342
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:37,035
but just wait till old Abe
gets ahold of him on slavery!

343
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:38,634
You're crazy!

344
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:42,673
Lincoln has no more chance of beating
Douglas for Senate than l have.

345
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:45,556
He only went to school for three months.

346
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:08,192
There must be no issue of slavery.

347
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:14,873
We must face the facts.

348
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:26,596
l'll run Mr. Lincoln out of this campaign.

349
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,391
l will not throw mud.

350
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:49,234
Let each State mind its own business
and this Republic can exist forever...

351
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:54,551
divided into free and slave states.

352
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:11,957
We will not allow
the extensión of slavery to any State.

353
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:18,713
We will not allow
the secessión of any State.

354
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:29,074
Above all and before all,
the Unión must be preserved.

355
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:39,596
A house divided
against itself must fall!

356
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:52,755
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

357
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:56,755
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

358
00:31:57,480 --> 00:32:04,670
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

359
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:20,189
Mary...

360
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:30,239
l'm home, Mary.

361
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:39,070
You must be tired, Mr, Lincoln.

362
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:42,754
Sit down.

363
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:58,591
You just ait right here.
l'll get your supper for you in a minute.

364
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:16,513
Billy, l feel like
the little boy who stubbed his toe.

365
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:19,478
lt hurt too bad to laugh,
and he was too big to cry.

366
00:33:21,920 --> 00:33:24,992
l'm fifty years old, Billy,
and a failure in everything.

367
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,593
lf l died today,
nobody'd ever know l'd lived.

368
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,074
Come in.

369
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:39,513
Mr. Lincoln,
l want you to meet Mr. Pell

370
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:43,157
one of the most important
men in Eastern politics.

371
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,673
- l'm pleased to meet you, Mr. Pell.
- l'm honored, indeed, Mr. Lincoln.

372
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:49,434
- Meet my partner, Mr, Herndon.
- How do you do, Mr. Herndon?

373
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:50,709
Happy to meet you, sir.

374
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,076
- Won't you sit down, gentlemen?
- Thank you.

375
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:58,271
Mr. Lincoln, your campaign against
Douglas has made you a national figure.

376
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:03,119
l'm here to ask you if you will consider
being the Republican party's candidate

377
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:05,078
for the presidency.

378
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:15,033
Did you say a failure in everything?

379
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:21,431
- A telegram for you, Mr. Fell.
- Oh thank you.

380
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:31,714
Mr. Lincoln, you know
ever since John Brown's raid,

381
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:35,796
the South has been infuriated,
the East on the verge of revolt,

382
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:38,275
and now New York
threatens to quit the Unión.

383
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:40,271
No, no New York mustn't do that.

384
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:44,435
We must keep the front door on the hinge.
There can be no secessión.

385
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:49,155
The Unión must be preserved.

386
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:54,799
The crisis is at hand, Mr.Lincoln,
and we believe you are the man.

387
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:04,398
Gentlemen,
l feel deeply grateful.

388
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:09,552
Paw, Maw says if you don't come on home,
you won't get no supper.

389
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:15,394
"l have another crisis; the soup and
the country are boiling over together!"

390
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:17,318
Maw's boiling too!

391
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:23,315
lt needs deep consideratión.

392
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:27,989
Well, Mr.Lincoln,
mayn't we meet you at our hotel later?

393
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:32,836
- l'll be there within the hour?
- Thank you.

394
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:36,152
Come on, Paw, we're hungry.

395
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:57,272
They've started it.
This is gonna mean war!

396
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,152
This darkio saw it himself.

397
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:03,878
Brown and a gang of Abolxitionists
have captured the armory at Harper's Ferry!

398
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:07,358
They're arming the slaves
to rise up and murder us all.

399
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:10,160
They gived us all rifles.

400
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,594
And what'd you do with yours?

401
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:17,796
What'd l do? l trowed it down,
and l say, 'Feet, you travel'

402
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:20,998
- They can't invade Virginia.
- No!

403
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:23,760
Boys, go home and git your guns.

404
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,154
What's all this talk about guns?

405
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:26,958
This thing has gone far enough.

406
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:29,913
We'll be murdered
in our beds by our own slaves.

407
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:33,356
Pardon me, ladies,
while l find out about this desecratión.

408
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,869
- John Brown, eh?
- Abolitionists!

409
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:37,229
lt's an outrage!

410
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,271
Outrage isn't the word.

411
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:46,754
l'll shoot on sight every Abolitionist
who dares defile the soil of old Virginia.

412
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:50,273
- Who's he?
- That's the actor, John Wilkes Booth.

413
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,750
He can't act
but the women don't know it.

414
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:57,392
All right, men, get your guns
and we'll meet at the square!

415
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:01,270
At the square!

416
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,796
Can't say much for her dispositión!

417
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:38,393
Hush! She may hear you.

418
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:40,949
Soldiers, indeed!
They can't even carry trunks.

419
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:43,430
Here you no, the stupid-looking one

420
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:46,598
put that over there...
and you... idiot

421
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:49,194
don't look at me like
a duck in a thunderstorm!

422
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,710
Hurry... hurry!
Will you put them in there?

423
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:55,276
l never saw such a lot of incompetents.

424
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:58,194
And as for you with the whiskers,
l told you to put it in there.

425
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,638
Oh, is it going to take forever?

426
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:07,231
Thank heavens, that's the last!

427
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,554
lmbeciles!

428
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:11,839
Well, Mary, we're here.

429
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:15,869
Thanks to me! lf it wasn't for my advice,
you'd be out in Oregon, chopping trees.

430
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,510
Yes, you're always right, Mary.

431
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:27,315
l've found out one thing, Lincoln.

432
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:30,709
Servants here are no better
than they are in Springfield.

433
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:36,034
This place
hasn't been cleaned in a year.

434
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:41,070
Why, Mr. President!

435
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:45,548
Huh?

436
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:55,919
Then we agree that the situatión
of our country is ominous.

437
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,991
- Most alarming.
- Certainly.

438
00:38:58,160 --> 00:39:01,789
We agree that we must yield
to the demands of the South

439
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:05,479
and evacuate Fort Sumter.

440
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,231
- Absolutely.
- lt's the only solutión.

441
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,799
That must be done.

442
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:14,271
We agree that our President
must be firmly guided by us.

443
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:21,472
That we must make every effort
to control his inexperienced judgment.

444
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:25,556
- We certainly must.
- Yes.

445
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:32,634
Gentlemen...

446
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,716
- Mr. President.
- Good morning, Mr. President.

447
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:36,154
Thank you, Hay.

448
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:15,873
Thank you, gentlemen...

449
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:25,796
l will shoulder all responsibilities.
The relief shall go to Fort Sumter.

450
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,198
That means war.

451
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:34,552
Mr. Seward, l am a man of peace,

452
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:39,277
but the Unión shall be preserved.

453
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,877
Seventy-five thousand...

454
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:13,233
lt might be difficult
to get that many volunteers.

455
00:42:13,520 --> 00:42:21,518
- Glory, glory Hallelujah,-
- Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

456
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:29,878
- Glory, glory Hallelujah!-
- His soul is marching on!-

