465
00:43:57,360 --> 00:44:02,388
President, the people demand a victory,
and we've got to take Richmond.

466
00:44:10,760 --> 00:44:14,196
The country is discouraged.
We must do something.

467
00:44:14,800 --> 00:44:17,268
That reminds me of a story...

468
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:20,479
about a man building
a boat to cross a river.

469
00:44:21,160 --> 00:44:24,311
He got impatient
building the boat and started swimming.

470
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:27,473
Well, sir, what happened?

471
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:29,794
He drowned.

472
00:44:30,680 --> 00:44:34,468
We've got to be careful
not to drown this country.

473
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:46,798
Ready here!
Ready here!

474
00:44:48,160 --> 00:44:49,434
- Quartermaster General.
- Yes, sir.

475
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:51,039
Ready here!
Ready here!

476
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:56,150
- Ready here!
- Sergeant, l'm going out.

477
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:00,791
- How did you make out?
- Make out?

478
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:02,553
He darned near kissed me.

479
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:04,238
- Who?
- The Secretary of War.

480
00:45:04,480 --> 00:45:07,472
We're just licking
the tar out of thorn all along the line.

481
00:45:08,120 --> 00:45:09,314
- Who's next?
- l am.

482
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:12,318
l hope it's for the President.
l'd like to sec his face

483
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:13,754
when he gets the good news.

484
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:17,390
Ready here! Commissary.

485
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:20,831
For General Scott.
Marked private.

486
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:22,348
Rush it it's victory!

487
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:28,872
General Scott, what news?

488
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:31,350
We're winning, sir. l'm sure of it.

489
00:45:32,040 --> 00:45:35,430
- l wish...
- Come in.

490
00:45:43,600 --> 00:45:46,433
Rebel resistance broken at Bulll Run,-

491
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:50,356
our army sweeping everything before it.-

492
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:56,274
President, if we can
capture Richmond now,

493
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:58,431
it means the end of the war.

494
00:45:58,600 --> 00:46:01,353
- Ah, thank God.
- And you, sir...

495
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:05,555
this victory will silence
your enemies forever

496
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:09,595
and you will be
the greatest president in our history.

497
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:13,036
lt doesn't matter
what they think of me, General.

498
00:46:14,520 --> 00:46:16,112
- We will have saved the Unión.
- Yes.

499
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:22,795
General, would you mind
letting me have that telegram?

500
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,950
l'd like to show it
to Mrs. Lincoln myself.

501
00:46:25,160 --> 00:46:27,549
Why, certainly, not, Mr. President.

502
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:32,115
And would you mind
not calling me 'Mr.President'..

503
00:46:33,080 --> 00:46:34,513
just Lincoln.

504
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:37,715
All right, Lincoln.

505
00:46:45,840 --> 00:46:48,354
Ready here!
Headquarters!

506
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:50,990
Sergeant, all messages
for General Scott, hold.

507
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,798
All messages for General Scott hold.

508
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,997
All messages for General Scott hold.

509
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:57,669
Attentión! Commanding officer.

510
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:03,354
At ease!

511
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:04,714
Ready here!

512
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:08,229
Bad news?
Give it to me.

513
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:17,471
Attentión the President!

514
00:47:18,280 --> 00:47:19,474
At ease!

515
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:22,150
Well, General, what news now?

516
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:25,912
And the first reports?

517
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:29,871
Over-confidence.

518
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:34,911
Yes, l should have known.

519
00:47:46,360 --> 00:47:48,555
lmpossible to reform lines.-

520
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:51,591
The men are a confused mob,-

521
00:47:52,120 --> 00:47:53,917
entirely demoralized.-

522
00:47:54,520 --> 00:47:58,399
You must make every effort
to save Washington.

523
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:16,268
- ¡1!
- ¡2!

524
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:17,714
- ¡3!
- ¡4!

525
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:18,869
- ¡1!
- ¡2!

526
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:20,194
- ¡3!
- ¡4!

527
00:48:20,320 --> 00:48:21,469
- ¡1!
- ¡2!

528
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:22,794
- ¡3!
- ¡4!

529
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:24,228
- ¡1!
- ¡2!

530
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:25,953
Battalion!

531
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:27,873
On right into line, March!

532
00:48:28,080 --> 00:48:29,354
Company, halt!

533
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:30,914
Left turn!

534
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:34,079
Right turn!

535
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:35,634
Halt!

536
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:41,197
First Company, right by fours.

537
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:43,394
Halt!

538
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,153
Forward!

539
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:50,236
Halt!

540
00:48:50,400 --> 00:48:51,958
Forward!

541
00:49:16,760 --> 00:49:18,751
Well, they're gathering.

542
00:49:26,480 --> 00:49:27,754
The reserves are gathering, sir.

543
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:30,474
- How many regulars can we muster?
- About five thousand.

544
00:49:31,520 --> 00:49:33,317
- Volunteers?
- Doubtful, sir.

545
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:35,392
Can we hold Washington?

546
00:49:35,720 --> 00:49:36,994
We'll do our best sir.

547
00:49:43,840 --> 00:49:46,479
Mr. Hay, is it true
we have to get out of Washington?

548
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:47,794
lt is very serious, madam.

549
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:50,600
For heaven's sake,
what sort of an army have we anyhow?

550
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:52,392
They did the best
they could, Mrs.Lincoln.

551
00:49:52,560 --> 00:49:53,913
They might have considered us.

552
00:49:54,040 --> 00:49:55,996
lt'll take forever
to get those trunks packed.

553
00:49:56,160 --> 00:49:58,879
l'm sorry, madam, for all of us.

554
00:50:04,360 --> 00:50:07,113
Mr.Lincoln, l hear we're leaving.

555
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:09,996
Just a moment, Mary, please.

556
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:12,869
After all the trouble we had getting here,

557
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:16,118
l must say we've had a very short stay.

558
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:21,635
Mary, l've hung up my hat right here,

559
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:24,718
and here it stays till
they knock it off with a bayonet.

560
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:31,717
From now on, Mary,
l'm going to run this war.

561
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:41,955
March! Halt!

562
00:50:43,200 --> 00:50:44,952
Headquarters,
Post Number Four.

563
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:49,393
Halt! Guard.

564
00:50:49,840 --> 00:50:51,432
Forward March!

565
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:01,719
Counsel of the accused,

566
00:51:02,160 --> 00:51:04,628
have you nothing further
to say in defense of the prisoner?

567
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:10,035
The court finds you guilty
and the sentence death.

568
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:18,389
- Just a minute.
- The President... attentión!

569
00:51:25,240 --> 00:51:27,515
You must pardon me,
gentlemen, for this intrusión.

570
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:33,071
l overheard one of our soldiers
sentenced to death.

571
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:37,239
Yes, Mr.President.
A bad example of cowardice and desertión.

572
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:43,594
Well, young man, tell me about it.

573
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:49,955
l think the findings
of the court were just, sir.

574
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,592
That all you have to say?

575
00:51:54,920 --> 00:51:58,390
Sire, it was our first big battle.

576
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:01,316
We were trying to take a stone wall.

577
00:52:02,280 --> 00:52:04,350
We'd been trying,
it seems, for years...

578
00:52:04,520 --> 00:52:05,748
Go on.

579
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:08,960
Finally, though, we got there.

580
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:12,714
l was fighting bayonets.

581
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:15,079
We were all crazy...

582
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,193
on top of the wall...

583
00:52:18,080 --> 00:52:19,229
Yes?

584
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:24,670
There was my boyhood chum,
looking up at me from the ground.

585
00:52:26,200 --> 00:52:32,389
Not alive,
we had killed him a long time ago,

586
00:52:32,920 --> 00:52:35,195
but l knew him.

587
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:36,954
And then?

588
00:52:37,920 --> 00:52:40,957
l guess l went really crazy, sir.

589
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:44,629
That's all.

590
00:52:44,880 --> 00:52:47,189
The captain reports
that you threw your rifle away.

591
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:50,638
Yes, sir. That must be right, sir.

592
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:53,037
Making excuses, Colton?

593
00:52:53,280 --> 00:52:54,713
No, sir only...

594
00:52:55,600 --> 00:52:57,192
get it over with, quick!

595
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:08,872
Hanging, killing, blood.

596
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,314
l'm tired.

597
00:53:25,400 --> 00:53:29,188
But my generals are right,
we must maintain discipline.

598
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:30,869
That's all.

599
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:35,668
Wait a minute.

600
00:53:37,400 --> 00:53:38,628
Bring that young man back.

601
00:53:42,840 --> 00:53:44,034
l have it!

602
00:53:45,280 --> 00:53:48,158
- lt's a leg case.
- l beg your pardon, sir?

603
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:50,831
Leg case... yes, yes,

604
00:53:50,960 --> 00:53:55,192
my shelves are full of them,
but not quite like this one.

605
00:53:57,440 --> 00:54:00,989
lf the Lord Almighty
gives a man a cowardly pair of legs,

606
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:02,873
and that man gets frightened,

607
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:07,073
he can't help his legs
running away with him, can he?

608
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,951
Young man, l'm going to pardon you.

609
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:19,871
Go back and do your duty.

610
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:24,390
Oh, l will, sir! l will!

611
00:54:25,640 --> 00:54:26,993
l'm trusting you.

612
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:34,034
Well, Senator?

613
00:54:35,760 --> 00:54:39,230
Mr. President, my state of New York

614
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:42,074
is crying out
against this endless slaughter.

615
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:43,713
And mine, sir.

616
00:54:47,080 --> 00:54:51,631
They're holding services here today
for those who were sacrificed,

617
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:54,713
as they are everywhere.

618
00:54:55,200 --> 00:54:57,350
From the East to the West, sir.

619
00:54:57,600 --> 00:54:58,919
lt can't go on, sir.

620
00:55:00,920 --> 00:55:03,275
New England,the West,

621
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:08,960
the entire country are in mourning
for this useless waste of lives.

622
00:55:11,240 --> 00:55:14,994
Let the Southern States
go there wat, Mr. President,

623
00:55:15,600 --> 00:55:16,669
and we will go ours.

624
00:55:16,920 --> 00:55:18,638
But l tell you, Mr. President...

625
00:55:18,960 --> 00:55:22,555
- ...out of the wilderness,-
- out of the wilderness.-

626
00:55:22,800 --> 00:55:26,759
- Old Abe Lincoln-
- came out of the wilderness,-

627
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,912
down in lllinois.-

628
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:34,645
Daddy, mother won't let me stay up.

629
00:55:34,680 --> 00:55:37,319
She wants me to go to bed,
and l don't want to.

630
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:40,830
Don't you think it's time
for little boys to be in bed, Tad?

631
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:44,317
- But l want to stay with you.
- But your mother?

632
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:47,552
lf you say so, she can't make me.

633
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:49,159
You're the President.

634
00:55:50,480 --> 00:55:55,315
You're the only person in the country
who thinks l should have any authority.

635
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:03,037
- Run along now.
- No.

636
00:56:03,320 --> 00:56:07,313
l want to stay with you.
Please, can't l, daddy?

637
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:11,798
No, we're very busy here now, Tad.
Run along.

638
00:56:12,400 --> 00:56:13,719
All right, daddy.

639
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:19,512
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

640
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:22,079
Sleep tight.

641
00:56:22,440 --> 00:56:23,589
Goodnight...

642
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:34,558
Gentlemen,
don't you suppose my heart bleeds

643
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:37,718
for all the sorrows
this war has brought upon us?

644
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:43,431
Do you suppose there is a human being
who wants peace more than l do.

645
00:56:44,920 --> 00:56:47,229
But we want lasting peace,

646
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:52,793
and we can have that only
by preserving the Unión.

647
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:03,593
And, gentlemen...

648
00:57:04,800 --> 00:57:07,553
the Unión is going to be preserved!

649
00:57:13,080 --> 00:57:17,631
- And by virtue of the power,-
- and for the purpose aforesaid,-

650
00:57:18,520 --> 00:57:22,638
- l do order and declare-
- that all persons held as slaves -

651
00:57:22,880 --> 00:57:26,555
- within said designated states-
- and parts of states-

652
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:30,676
- are henceforward-
- and forever shall be...-

653
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:32,389
free.-

654
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:52,916
Well, gentlemen, it is done.

655
00:58:11,440 --> 00:58:13,476
- More bad news, Hay?
- l'm afraid there is.

656
00:58:13,600 --> 00:58:14,749
Well, let's have it.

657
00:58:14,920 --> 00:58:17,115
The Secret Service
reports that there are 600.000

658
00:58:17,520 --> 00:58:19,795
pperheads in the North and under cath and arme

659
00:58:19,960 --> 00:58:21,279
- To get me?
- Yes.

660
00:58:22,440 --> 00:58:24,192
That many ought
to keep me dodging.

661
00:58:24,440 --> 00:58:26,590
We're taking
every precautión to guard you.

662
00:58:28,240 --> 00:58:29,673
Where are they mostly?

663
00:58:30,520 --> 00:58:34,274
Ohio has one 100.000 armed men
ready to rise up and depose you.

664
00:58:34,560 --> 00:58:36,551
lllionois, 135.000.

665
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:41,475
lllinois,
my old stamping ground...

666
00:58:43,480 --> 00:58:48,554
That makes me feel badly.
You mustn't tell Mary.

667
00:58:48,720 --> 00:58:51,871
But Mr. President,
we are worried about you.

668
00:58:52,920 --> 00:58:57,232
Don't mind me, Hay.
Go on to bed, you're tired.

669
00:59:25,600 --> 00:59:27,955
Lincoln, come on to bed.

670
00:59:29,280 --> 00:59:30,679
l'm worried, Mary.

671
00:59:31,640 --> 00:59:35,633
You can't win this war worrying and
walking around in your stocking feet.

672
00:59:36,480 --> 00:59:37,799
l can't sleep.

673
00:59:38,640 --> 00:59:43,953
Neither can l. At least we could sleep
in Springfield, couldn't we?

674
00:59:45,600 --> 00:59:48,831
Did we ever sleep?

675
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,556
Now, stand still.

676
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:19,478
l've got it, Mary.

677
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:25,118
l've found the man to win this war

678
01:00:27,320 --> 01:00:30,995
and his name is Grant.

679
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:45,554
l'm sorry, Mr. President, but smoking
is one of my most persistent habits.

680
01:00:46,840 --> 01:00:49,149
And winning victories is another.

681
01:00:50,680 --> 01:00:51,908
Thank you.

682
01:00:55,400 --> 01:00:57,311
Then you do believe in me, Sir?

683
01:00:58,320 --> 01:00:59,833
l sent for you.

684
01:01:03,480 --> 01:01:07,758
General, the North is desperate.

685
01:01:08,680 --> 01:01:10,432
We need you.

686
01:01:18,520 --> 01:01:22,229
And, should l assume command,
there will be no interference?

687
01:01:22,360 --> 01:01:24,874
None. l promise you that.

688
01:01:27,000 --> 01:01:28,228
Grant,...

689
01:01:29,200 --> 01:01:31,919
Lieutenant-General is
the highest army command

690
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:33,872
the President can bestow.

691
01:01:35,320 --> 01:01:38,198
We haven't had one
since General Washington.

692
01:01:40,080 --> 01:01:42,719
He was a fair sort of a soldier too.

693
01:01:44,680 --> 01:01:46,398
Lieutenant-General Grant,...

694
01:01:47,720 --> 01:01:50,075
my orders are: Win the War.

695
01:01:52,280 --> 01:01:55,113
l'll give my best, Mr. President.

696
01:01:55,920 --> 01:01:57,512
l know you will.

697
01:01:59,760 --> 01:02:03,116
Unfortunately many of us
have failed to recognize

698
01:02:04,200 --> 01:02:06,714
a great Confederate Soldier.

699
01:02:07,440 --> 01:02:08,919
Lee.

700
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,074
On the other hand, we have thus far

701
01:02:13,320 --> 01:02:17,791
failed to take advantage
of a great Northern Soldier.

702
01:02:17,920 --> 01:02:20,878
l hope l am not too late
in correcting the error.

703
01:02:22,440 --> 01:02:27,389
Mr. President,
l think it only fair to warn you

704
01:02:28,440 --> 01:02:30,635
that many people, don't approve of me.

705
01:02:30,920 --> 01:02:32,273
Nor of me.

706
01:02:33,840 --> 01:02:38,550
But rest assured
there will be no interference,

707
01:02:40,920 --> 01:02:42,512
no intrusión.

708
01:02:44,440 --> 01:02:47,432
Well, of all things!
Who locked this door?

709
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:49,794
My wife!

710
01:02:51,080 --> 01:02:52,479
All right, Mary.

711
01:02:58,640 --> 01:03:01,632
Land sakes!
Where did all the smoke come from?

712
01:03:01,800 --> 01:03:05,839
Mary, meet General Grant. Mrs. Lincoln.

713
01:03:06,520 --> 01:03:10,638
- lt's a pleasure to meet the first lady.
- Thank you.

714
01:03:11,360 --> 01:03:13,157
- l want to talk to you. Mr. Lincoln.
- But Mary, we...

715
01:03:13,320 --> 01:03:16,551
l want to talk to you about discharging
some of the servants in this house.

716
01:03:17,320 --> 01:03:20,790
l don't see how anybody
could talk in here with all this smoke.

717
01:03:22,520 --> 01:03:24,112
Why don't you open the window?

718
01:03:25,600 --> 01:03:26,749
l can't stand it!

719
01:03:27,480 --> 01:03:28,799
Pardon me, General.

720
01:03:29,760 --> 01:03:31,318
l'll have to talk to you later.

721
01:03:34,440 --> 01:03:37,671
- l'm very sorry if...
- There no apoligies, General.

722
01:03:39,000 --> 01:03:40,718
You've given me an idea.

723
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:44,396
l may take up smoking myself.

724
01:03:48,840 --> 01:03:50,558
But to resume, General.

725
01:03:52,040 --> 01:03:54,270
We will give you
all the help you need.

726
01:03:55,200 --> 01:03:58,510
Every man capable
of bearing arms shall go.

727
01:04:00,040 --> 01:04:02,315
We've got to win this war.

728
01:04:03,960 --> 01:04:07,635
lt is a duty we owe
the South as well as the North.

729
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:13,598
lt's a big job, Mr. President...
a big job.

730
01:04:14,200 --> 01:04:16,555
but thy will be done.

731
01:04:22,280 --> 01:04:23,793
Thy will be done.

732
01:04:30,320 --> 01:04:31,958
We're in a tight place now.

733
01:04:32,440 --> 01:04:34,431
Yes, we generally are, Stanton.

734
01:04:34,680 --> 01:04:37,240
Everything depends upon Sheridan.

735
01:04:37,640 --> 01:04:39,198
He's a fighting lrishman.

736
01:04:39,360 --> 01:04:41,078
Then why doesn't he fight?

737
01:04:48,000 --> 01:04:51,390
- One división Sheridan's -
- army routed.-

738
01:04:52,040 --> 01:04:55,669
Now trying to hold left flank.-

739
01:04:58,600 --> 01:05:02,479
Oh, the blood it takes
to hold this Unión together.

740
01:05:02,880 --> 01:05:08,716
lt will undo everything
Grant has done. lt's hopeless.

741
01:05:09,200 --> 01:05:10,633
l don't think so...

742
01:05:11,840 --> 01:05:16,072
Before each victory l've had
a visión of a ship with white sails.

743
01:05:18,440 --> 01:05:20,556
That visión has just conic to me.

744
01:05:21,840 --> 01:05:25,674
With all respect,
l'd rather trade your ship

745
01:05:26,120 --> 01:05:28,236
for good news from Sheridan.

746
01:05:33,520 --> 01:05:35,476
ls that General Sheridan in there?

747
01:05:36,360 --> 01:05:37,998
Sure 'tis General Sheridan.

748
01:05:51,760 --> 01:05:53,512
Doesn't that sound like cannon fire?

749
01:05:56,600 --> 01:05:58,397
l don't hear anything, sir.

750
01:06:19,600 --> 01:06:21,033
Hey, come here.

751
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:25,045
Have you good ears?

752
01:06:25,080 --> 01:06:26,718
Pretty good when they're washed.

753
01:06:27,840 --> 01:06:29,034
Then try them.

754
01:06:30,000 --> 01:06:31,752
Do you hear anything like cannon fire?

755
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:40,877
lt's cannon all right,
over by the swamp.

756
01:06:41,120 --> 01:06:42,997
They may have caught
General Wright by surprise!

757
01:06:43,920 --> 01:06:45,069
Mount those shorses!

758
01:06:57,120 --> 01:07:02,194
- Sheridan's entire army-
- has met an overwhelming defeat.-

759
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:10,594
lncredible.
And no word from Sheridan.

760
01:07:12,160 --> 01:07:13,912
l'm afraid he was away.

761
01:07:17,000 --> 01:07:19,992
lt means the defeat of all our plans.

762
01:07:20,560 --> 01:07:24,553
Yes, for we'll have
to withdraw Grant from Richmond

763
01:07:25,240 --> 01:07:27,117
to protect Washington.

764
01:07:34,480 --> 01:07:37,199
Come on, boys! Come on!

765
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:16,310
General,
the right wing is in full retreat.

766
01:09:16,600 --> 01:09:17,874
lmpossible to hold our positión, sir.

767
01:09:18,160 --> 01:09:21,789
Tell Colonel Tolliver
to reform and hold at all costs.

768
01:09:21,920 --> 01:09:23,114
We're going back!

769
01:09:29,080 --> 01:09:30,399
Officers, reform your men!

770
01:09:30,680 --> 01:09:31,954
We're going back!

771
01:09:47,680 --> 01:09:51,559
- Come on boys, let's go!
- Let's go, boys!

772
01:09:53,080 --> 01:09:55,230
Forward!
Forward to victory!

773
01:10:13,760 --> 01:10:17,116
- Down with, the traitor,-
- up with the star!-

774
01:10:17,400 --> 01:10:19,231
- While we rally-
- 'round the flag boys,-

775
01:10:19,560 --> 01:10:21,118
- We'll rally-
- once again,-

776
01:10:21,520 --> 01:10:24,478
shouting the battle cry of freedom!-

777
01:10:25,200 --> 01:10:26,918
Yes, we'll rally 'round the flag, boys-

778
01:10:27,160 --> 01:10:28,832
We'll rally once again,-

779
01:10:29,240 --> 01:10:32,710
Shouting the battle cry of freedom,-

780
01:10:33,200 --> 01:10:36,795
- We will rally from the hillside,-
- We'll gather from the plain.-

781
01:10:37,280 --> 01:10:40,829
Shouting the battle cry of freedom,-

782
01:10:41,400 --> 01:10:45,359
- The Unión forever,-
- hurrah, boys, hurrah!-

783
01:10:45,560 --> 01:10:48,996
- Sown with the traitor,-
- up with the star.-

784
01:10:49,120 --> 01:10:51,315
While we rally round the flag boys,-

785
01:10:51,560 --> 01:10:53,391
We'll rally once again,-

786
01:10:53,680 --> 01:10:57,116
Shouting the battle cry of freedom,-

787
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:13,828
Arrived in time to reform forces.-

788
01:11:14,360 --> 01:11:15,918
Have struck the enemy-

789
01:11:16,680 --> 01:11:20,150
- and have won an
overwhelming victory. Sheridan.-

790
01:11:21,520 --> 01:11:22,748
l knew it.

791
01:11:23,920 --> 01:11:25,148
l knew it...

792
01:11:30,720 --> 01:11:36,670
Better and better. Look! Here.
Tremendous number of prisoners.

793
01:11:38,480 --> 01:11:39,879
Prisoners?

794
01:11:41,600 --> 01:11:45,878
l hope there's nothing
but prisoners from now on.

795
01:11:50,600 --> 01:11:53,956
The ship, Stanton!

796
01:11:55,360 --> 01:11:56,952
Yes, Mr. President,

797
01:11:57,960 --> 01:11:59,279
and Sheridan!

798
01:13:05,880 --> 01:13:07,313
Surrender...

799
01:13:08,720 --> 01:13:10,711
my poor army!

800
01:13:12,160 --> 01:13:15,311
l'd rather die a thousand deaths
than do that to them.

801
01:13:15,760 --> 01:13:19,309
There, General,
you must lie down and rest.

802
01:13:21,920 --> 01:13:23,194
Rest...

803
01:13:25,240 --> 01:13:27,117
that's a beautiful word...

804
01:14:08,760 --> 01:14:12,639
They've caught a spy and they want
the order for his executión approved.

805
01:14:32,320 --> 01:14:33,469
Colonel Marshall...

806
01:14:34,920 --> 01:14:36,114
who was that?

807
01:14:36,320 --> 01:14:38,959
- Only a courier, sir.
- What did he want?

808
01:14:39,080 --> 01:14:42,152
They've caught a spy.
l approved the executión order, sir.

809
01:14:42,680 --> 01:14:43,874
Colonel,...

810
01:14:44,960 --> 01:14:49,795
the only reason for shooting a spy
is the protectión of an army, isn't it?

811
01:14:50,200 --> 01:14:51,428
Yes, sir.

812
01:14:52,440 --> 01:14:53,919
Well,...

813
01:14:55,160 --> 01:14:58,516
you and l know
that this army can't exist much longer.

814
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:01,954
lsn't that right?

815
01:15:03,440 --> 01:15:04,714
Yes, sir.

816
01:15:05,360 --> 01:15:09,114
That is why l am unwilling
that there shall be a single life lost

817
01:15:09,760 --> 01:15:11,193
unnecessarily.

818
01:15:15,680 --> 01:15:16,908
Colonel...

819
01:15:17,280 --> 01:15:21,239
l wonder if you'd mind
countermanding that order.

820
01:15:23,280 --> 01:15:24,554
l will.
Yes, sir.

821
01:16:05,960 --> 01:16:07,359
Tired, Grant?

822
01:16:09,000 --> 01:16:10,479
Not much.

823
01:16:30,480 --> 01:16:32,357
Mr. President, we have them.

824
01:16:33,280 --> 01:16:36,033
lt can only last a few days more.

825
01:16:37,400 --> 01:16:40,551
General Sherman and l are glad
of this chance to talk with you.

826
01:16:41,680 --> 01:16:45,673
The Unión...
we've saved it at last.

827
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:47,912
They must surrender soon.

828
01:16:49,080 --> 01:16:50,308
The Unión...

829
01:16:51,600 --> 01:16:53,397
We'll have 'em all back...

830
01:16:54,520 --> 01:16:58,115
United, free...
one Country.

831
01:16:58,840 --> 01:17:00,558
And meanwhile, Mr. President?

832
01:17:01,720 --> 01:17:05,838
l've heard the country
wishes all rebel property confiscated

833
01:17:06,840 --> 01:17:11,755
and the rebel generals,
such as Lee, shot for treason.

834
01:17:12,920 --> 01:17:15,070
He's put up a grand battle.

835
01:17:17,280 --> 01:17:20,397
And they've robbed
the cradle and the grave, sir.

836
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:24,477
Lee is fighting with his last breath.

837
01:17:26,800 --> 01:17:28,392
Shoot Robert E. Lee?

838
01:17:29,440 --> 01:17:32,398
Someone will have to shoot
Abraham Lincoln first.

839
01:17:34,280 --> 01:17:36,555
They're rebels, not traitors.

840
01:17:37,960 --> 01:17:40,428
And their horses and baggage, sir?

841
01:17:41,920 --> 01:17:44,195
They'll need them
for the spring plowing.

842
01:17:45,360 --> 01:17:47,112
Let 'em keep 'em and get to work.

843
01:17:48,360 --> 01:17:49,759
Very good, sir.

844
01:17:50,600 --> 01:17:53,194
Just one thing more, Mr.President...

845
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:57,794
the head of the rebel government
Jefferson Davis?

846
01:18:00,680 --> 01:18:01,954
Jefferson Davis...

847
01:18:02,480 --> 01:18:04,232
Do you wish his capture?

848
01:18:07,360 --> 01:18:09,555
That reminds me of a story.

849
01:18:10,680 --> 01:18:12,557
We had a terrible drunkard once

850
01:18:14,680 --> 01:18:15,954
in Springfield.

851
01:18:17,440 --> 01:18:19,590
Finally he signed the pledge.

852
01:18:19,680 --> 01:18:21,238
Next day he got thirsty

853
01:18:21,400 --> 01:18:23,709
and went to a bar
and ordered a lemonade.

854
01:18:24,760 --> 01:18:29,276
While the bartender was fixing it,
the old drunk got sadder and sadder.

855
01:18:30,600 --> 01:18:32,955
Finally he leaned over
and said to the bartender,

856
01:18:34,560 --> 01:18:37,791
"Mike, while you're fixin' that,

857
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:40,071
couldn't you put
a nice little shot of whiskey in,

858
01:18:40,320 --> 01:18:41,958
unbeknownst to meself?"

859
01:18:42,600 --> 01:18:43,919
Well, sir?

860
01:18:46,000 --> 01:18:48,309
Couldn't you sort
of lot Jeff Davis escape,

861
01:18:49,720 --> 01:18:51,472
unbeknownst to yourselves?

862
01:18:53,080 --> 01:18:54,513
We'll do our part, sir.

863
01:18:58,680 --> 01:19:02,468
We're going to take them back
as though they'd never been away.

864
01:19:10,920 --> 01:19:12,353
Lincoln...

865
01:19:16,640 --> 01:19:18,392
He freed the negroes.

866
01:19:21,400 --> 01:19:24,392
He's supressed
the right of a trail by jury.

867
01:19:27,920 --> 01:19:29,353
He muzzled the press!

868
01:19:34,640 --> 01:19:36,949
Now, wiht the oid of this "butternuts",

869
01:19:37,800 --> 01:19:39,995
his army and his negroes,
he make himself

870
01:19:40,080 --> 01:19:41,559
King of the América.

871
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:45,194
Lincoln!

872
01:19:50,480 --> 01:19:51,879
l drink to him...

873
01:19:55,160 --> 01:19:57,879
and his domatión!

874
01:20:03,400 --> 01:20:04,753
Right,...

875
01:20:05,040 --> 01:20:06,439
you're right.

876
01:20:07,080 --> 01:20:08,798
On my part...

877
01:20:14,160 --> 01:20:17,197
Go on,
you're among friends...

878
01:20:20,120 --> 01:20:24,272
The man who kills Abraham Lincoln

879
01:20:25,480 --> 01:20:27,311
will be inmortal.

880
01:20:30,120 --> 01:20:31,473
Now, listen...

881
01:20:37,600 --> 01:20:39,113
l have a plan...

882
01:20:40,760 --> 01:20:41,954
and l'm going in.

883
01:20:54,720 --> 01:20:57,314
Do you mind my smoking, Mrs. Lincoln?

884
01:20:57,640 --> 01:20:59,756
No, not much.

885
01:21:01,960 --> 01:21:05,396
You don't know how glad we all are
that you were reelected, Mr. President.

886
01:21:06,000 --> 01:21:07,399
l'm sure this lady will be glad

887
01:21:07,640 --> 01:21:09,153
to spend four more years
in the White House.

888
01:21:09,280 --> 01:21:11,669
Glad? l've just hired two new maids.

889
01:21:14,160 --> 01:21:17,550
Lincoln, will you ever learn
to keep your feet in shoes?

890
01:21:19,760 --> 01:21:23,196
Mrs. Lincoln,
have you met General Grant?

891
01:21:23,440 --> 01:21:26,716
l met him. lt took us a week
to get the smoke out of the curtains.

892
01:21:29,800 --> 01:21:33,349
Yes, Oglesby, he's one
human being who has faults.

893
01:21:34,400 --> 01:21:36,960
A party of prohibitionists,
called on me the other day

894
01:21:37,240 --> 01:21:38,958
and complained about Grant's drinking.

895
01:21:40,000 --> 01:21:42,639
l told 'em if l knew what brand he uses,

896
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:45,115
l'd send barrels of it
to my other generals.

897
01:21:47,120 --> 01:21:49,031
Two new maids...

898
01:21:50,400 --> 01:21:52,994
lf we're going to be
here four more years...

899
01:21:55,120 --> 01:22:00,319
Four years...
four more years...

900
01:22:00,680 --> 01:22:03,797
Mr. Lincoln, don't you go thinking
about of those dreams again.

901
01:22:04,360 --> 01:22:08,433
You'll live two hundred and after
we'll celebrate it right over here,

902
01:22:09,200 --> 01:22:13,193
we'll travel around the worid
and have a nice long rest.

903
01:22:14,360 --> 01:22:17,989
Oh, Daddy!,
Would that be fun?

904
01:22:18,280 --> 01:22:21,875
- You're not going without me...?
- Why, of course not, Tad.

905
01:22:25,720 --> 01:22:30,077
You can depend on Mother Surratt,
and everything is straight with me.

906
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:33,719
l said l'd go through with it,
and l will.

907
01:22:34,600 --> 01:22:38,115
Tonight will be remembered
throughout the ages.

908
01:22:40,520 --> 01:22:43,432
l play my best part.

909
01:22:49,280 --> 01:22:52,795
How much better a dagger would look,

910
01:22:56,440 --> 01:22:58,556
Cassius used a dagger,

911
01:23:02,640 --> 01:23:04,358
but this is safer.

912
01:23:31,360 --> 01:23:34,318
- Speech!
- Speech!

913
01:23:39,880 --> 01:23:45,955
- Speech!
- Speech!

914
01:23:55,560 --> 01:23:58,870
Again l say,

915
01:24:00,680 --> 01:24:03,035
with malice toward none,

916
01:24:04,440 --> 01:24:06,715
with charity for all,

917
01:24:09,080 --> 01:24:10,877
with firmness in the right

918
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,594
as God gives us to see the right,

919
01:24:14,760 --> 01:24:19,151
we shall bind up
the natión's wounds and cherish peace.

920
01:24:23,720 --> 01:24:31,274
That government of the people,
by the people, for the people

921
01:24:32,360 --> 01:24:35,397
shall not perish from the earth.

922
01:24:39,920 --> 01:24:41,069
Thank you.

923
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:46,639
God bless you all.

924
01:25:01,040 --> 01:25:05,477
Mr. Lincoln, l'm just proud of you!

925
01:25:09,240 --> 01:25:12,118
- Peanuts, hold the horse for me?
- Yes.

926
01:25:17,280 --> 01:25:18,713
Will you be long, sir?

927
01:25:21,360 --> 01:25:22,952
No, not very long.

928
01:25:27,960 --> 01:25:31,032
Dundreary,
would you mind bringing me a wrap?

929
01:25:31,440 --> 01:25:32,919
l feel a draught.

930
01:25:33,280 --> 01:25:35,999
l'm afraid you must be mistaken.

931
01:25:36,680 --> 01:25:38,159
Mr. Lincoln...

932
01:25:38,680 --> 01:25:40,796
has just stopped the draft.

933
01:26:06,160 --> 01:26:08,958
l reckon l'm going
to feel right to home here, b'gosh!

934
01:26:10,120 --> 01:26:13,078
l would be too if it wasn't for
that 'ternal servant-critter

935
01:26:13,320 --> 01:26:15,675
with brass buttons on his coat.

936
01:26:19,880 --> 01:26:24,431
He just swells out his big bosom
like a turkey cock in layin' time,

937
01:26:26,000 --> 01:26:29,754
looks at me as if l meant
to esquatulate with the spoons.

938
01:26:32,640 --> 01:26:36,758
l reckon they don't know who they're
dealin' with, but l'll show 'em.

939
01:26:37,520 --> 01:26:40,637
l'm as obstinate
as Deacon Stumpp's forelock.

940
01:26:41,840 --> 01:26:44,035
"lt wouldn't lie down; it couldn't stand up,"

941
01:26:44,520 --> 01:26:47,557
wouldn't point forward and couldn't go backward.

942
01:26:49,600 --> 01:26:52,478
l don't know what
they're going to do with me,

943
01:26:53,120 --> 01:26:56,715
but whatever they do do
and wherever they put me,

944
01:26:57,000 --> 01:26:59,275
l hope it's outa
the reach of that jackass.

945
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:03,512
l'm a real hoss, l am,

946
01:27:03,600 --> 01:27:06,194
and l get kinda riley with them critters.

947
01:27:07,720 --> 01:27:11,872
They say l don't know
the manners of good society too,

948
01:27:13,480 --> 01:27:17,029
but l guess l know enough
to turn that old gal inside out,

949
01:27:18,240 --> 01:27:20,470
the sock-dollaging old mantrap.

950
01:27:21,080 --> 01:27:23,958
But l dare no more kill her

951
01:27:24,240 --> 01:27:26,117
than l dare ask Queen Victoria

952
01:27:26,480 --> 01:27:28,914
to dance a Cape Cod reel.

953
01:27:39,240 --> 01:27:42,596
Sic semper tyrannis!

954
01:27:45,520 --> 01:27:48,398
Mr. Lincoln,
Mr. Lincoln has been shot!

955
01:28:02,400 --> 01:28:05,278
Get a doctor!
Somebody get a doctor!

956
01:29:15,840 --> 01:29:24,839
Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

957
01:29:25,640 --> 01:29:34,196
Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

958
01:29:34,920 --> 01:29:43,112
Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

959
01:29:43,440 --> 01:29:53,759
His soul is marching on!-

